Polyus Gold, AltynGroup Reach Accord on Mines, Kommersant Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-04-11T04:02:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/polyus-gold-altyngroup-reach-accord-on-mines-kommersant-says.html
Polyus Gold,  Russia ’s biggest
producer of precious metal, and AltynGroup reached agreement on
the sale of KazakhGold’s mines after almost a year of dispute,
 Kommersant  reported today, citing an unidentified shareholder of
the Russian company.  Polyus Gold agreed to sell production units of KazakhGold
that are under its control for $769 million to  Kazakhstan ’s
Assaulayev family, which owns AltynGroup. The latter agreed to
pay the price in several installments and to revoke criminal
allegations against top Polyus managers, according to the
report.  To contact the reporter on this story: Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow
   msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Claudia
Carpenter at   ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  